$ Oracle data file header
@ data file header

The data file header contains → development/Data/metadata about a → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/data:
  • Size of the data file
  • Last → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/transaction/SCN/checkpoint (see also → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/data/checkpoint).
  • *Absolute file number* that uniquely identifies the data file in the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database.
  • *Relative file number* that uniquely identifies the data file in the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/logical-structures/tablespace that it belongs to. 


sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/datafile/header[`v$datafile_header`]

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/fixed-tables/k/c/v/fh`
